    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="119"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d119">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.811/156.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Reinsch</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 2, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Minister of Agriculture and Commerce, in view of the terrible suffering affecting
                    over a million people which is again visiting Huai River region, has asked me to
                    communicate to you the request of the Chinese Government that the American Red
                    Cross use its good offices towards consummating Huai River loan immediately and
                    making an advance so that work of relief may be begun.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
